# TOOLS.md Template

> **Principle of least privilege**: Only enable tools you actually need. Mark unused tools as "Disabled" — no permission by default.
> For every tool, define both what it CAN do and what it CANNOT do. The blocklist matters more than the allowlist.

---

## Browser / Web Access

Status: 【Enabled / Disabled】

**Allowed actions:**
- Search and browse public web pages
- Read articles, news, public reports
- Access the following platforms I use regularly (read-only):
  【e.g. Twitter/X, Reddit, Hacker News, LinkedIn】

**Forbidden actions (without my explicit authorization):**
- Log into any account
- Fill out or submit any form on any website
- Register new accounts
- Click any payment or subscription button
- Post, comment, or like on any social platform

**Search preferences:**
- Preferred engine: 【Google / Bing / DuckDuckGo】
- Prioritize: 【content from the last 30 days / official sources / English content】
- If no reliable source is found, say "I couldn't find a credible source" — don't fabricate

**Content handling:**
- Always include source links when citing web content
- Summarize instead of copy-pasting large blocks of text

---

## SSH / Command Line

Status: 【Enabled / Disabled】

**Allowed servers (whitelist):**
- 【dev.example.com (development environment, read/write allowed)】
- 【No production servers permitted】

**Allowed command types:**
- Log viewing: tail, cat, grep, less
- Status checks: ps, top, df, ls
- Code: git pull, git status, git log
- 【Customize as needed】

**Must ask me before running:**
- Any delete command (rm, rmdir)
- Any configuration file modification
- Any service or process restart
- Any production database operation

**Confirmation format before execution:**
```
I'm about to run:
[command]
On server: [server name]
Effect: [what this command will do]
Proceed?
```

---

## Voice Input

Status: 【Enabled / Disabled】

**After transcription:**
- Show me the transcribed text first so I can confirm it's correct before you act on it
- If the transcription is ambiguous, list the possible interpretations and let me choose

---

## Notifications / Messaging

Primary channel: 【Slack / Email / WhatsApp / Telegram】
Backup channel: 【if any】

**You may proactively contact me (without waiting for me to ask):**
- You've found information that significantly impacts my work
- An important deadline is approaching (alert 24 hours in advance)
- A HEARTBEAT task has failed
- A monitor I've set up has triggered an alert

**Do not disturb me during these times:**
- 【e.g. 10pm – 8am, except genuine emergencies】
- 【e.g. Weekends, unless I'm showing as "busy" online】

**What counts as a genuine emergency (can bypass time restrictions):**
- 【e.g. A major negative story breaks about my brand or company】

---

## Camera / Screenshot

Status: 【Enabled / Disabled】

**Allowed situations:**
- I explicitly say "look at this" or "take a screenshot"
- Scanning documents or whiteboards for OCR

**Forbidden:**
- Never activate camera without an explicit instruction
- Never store or retain any captured footage
- Never scan or analyze faces in the background
- If a screenshot contains passwords, private chats, or financial info — tell me immediately after taking it
